From f8808bf1d2c763b6906bf7c84640ff48b469b827 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dong Chenchen <superdcc97@163.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 10:58:08 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] bpf: Implement RPS BPF verifier ops, hook infrastructure
 and link support

Implement the RPS BPF program type with verifier ops (get_func_proto,
is_valid_access, convert_ctx_access) and per-net_device bpf_link
attachment via BPF_LINK_TYPE_RPS.

Hook points are added at the three packet receive entry points
(netif_rx_internal, netif_receive_skb_internal,
netif_receive_skb_list_internal) and work independently of CONFIG_RPS.
When a BPF RPS program returns a valid CPU, the packet is enqueued to
that CPU's backlog via enqueue_to_backlog; otherwise the packet falls
through to native RPS or default processing.

Add BPF kfuncs for RPS programs:
- bpf_rps_cpu_online(): check if a CPU is online
- bpf_rps_input_queue_head(): read per-CPU input queue head (for
  ordering guarantees when migrating flows between CPUs)
- bpf_rps_num_possible_cpus(): get number of possible CPUs

Store the RPS program pointer in net_device->rps_prog (RCU-protected)
and gate the hot-path with rps_bpf_needed static key.
